1. Setting up Python  

   i) Step 1: Download Python
      - Visit the official [Python website](https://www.python.org/downloads/).
      - Download the latest version of Python for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux).

   ii) Step 2: Install Python
      - Run the installer you downloaded.
      - Important: Check the box that says "Add Python to PATH" before clicking Install.
      - Click "Customize Installation" if you want to adjust installation features (optional).
      - Complete the installation process.

   iii) Step 3: Verify Installation
      - Open a terminal or command prompt.
      - Type the following command to check the Python version:
        
        `python --version`

      - If installed correctly, it will display the Python version.

2. Python IDEs (VS Code, PyCharm)

   i) VS Code
      - Download VS Code from [here](https://code.visualstudio.com/).
      - Install the Python Extension.
      - Open VS Code and go to the Extensions Marketplace (Ctrl+Shift+X).
      - Search for "Python" and install the official Microsoft Python extension.
      - Set up a Python Interpreter:
        - Open a Python file or create a new one (e.g., `hello.py`).
        - Click on the bottom-left corner where it says "Select Interpreter".
        - Choose your installed Python version.

   ii) PyCharm
      - Download PyCharm from [here](https://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/).
      - Install PyCharm.
      - Run the installer and complete the setup.
      - Create a Python Project:
        - Open PyCharm and create a new project.
        - Select the Python interpreter (PyCharm usually auto-detects Python if installed).
        - Start coding:
          - Open the `main.py` file and start writing Python code.

3. Running Your First Python Program

   i) Create a Python File
      - Create a new file named `hello.py` in your preferred IDE or text editor.

   ii) Write Your Code
      - Add the following code:
        
        ```python
        print("Hello, World!")
        ```

   iii) Run the Python Program
      - Using VS Code:
        - Right-click in the editor and choose "Run Python File in Terminal".
        - Alternatively, press F5 to debug/run.

      - Using PyCharm:
        - Click the green play button in the top-right corner to run your program.

      - Using Command Prompt/Terminal:
        - Open a terminal, navigate to the file's location, and run:
          
          `python hello.py`

      - The output will display:
        
        ```
        Hello, World!
        ```


